text.section:
Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, a person may use reasonable force to remove from a motor vehicle a cat or dog left in the vehicle in violation of the provisions of subsection (a) of this section if the person is:
A law enforcement officer;
A public safety employee of the State or of a local governing body;
An animal control officer under the jurisdiction of the State or a local governing body;
An officer of a society or association, incorporated under the laws of this State for the prevention of cruelty to animals, authorized to make arrests under the provisions of § 10-609 of the Criminal Law Article; or
A volunteer or professional of a fire and rescue service.
